{{Infobox television | show_name = Rio Heroes | image = File:Rio_Heroes_title_card.png | genre = {{Plainlist| * [[Action (genre)|Action]] * [[Drama (film and television)|Drama]] * [[Sports film|Sports]] }} | creator = | based_on = | developer = | starring = {{Plain list| * [[Murilo Rosa]] * Juliana Araripe * Bruno Bellarmino * Roney Facchini * [[Priscila Fantin]] * Giovanni Gallo * Luiz Guilherme * Ronny Kriwat * Rafael Losso * Miguel Nader * Duda Nagle }} | composer = | country = Brazil | language = Portuguese | num_seasons = 1<!-- Update only after a new season begins --> | num_episodes = 5<!-- Update only after a new episode debuts --> | list_episodes = | executive_producer = | producer = | location = [[São Paulo]] | cinematography = André Modugno | editor = | camera = | runtime = | company = {{Plainlist| * Mixer Films * [[NBCUniversal]] * [[Fox Networks Group]] }} | distributor = [[Fox Networks Group]] | network = [[Fox Premium]] | picture_format = | audio_format = | first_aired = {{Start date|2018|2|24}} | last_aired = {{End date|present}} | related = | website = https://foxplay.com/br/show/FNGTVSeriesP6025 | website_title = Official website }}
'''''Rio Heroes''''' is a Brazilian [[Drama (film and television)|drama]] [[television program|television series]] produced by Mixer Films, [[NBCUniversal]], and [[Fox Networks Group]]. The series premiered on [[Fox Premium]] on February 24, 2018.
Starring [[Murilo Rosa]] in the lead role, ''Rio Heroes'' follows the story of Jorge Pereira, a [[jiu-jitsu]] athlete who did not conform to the increasing limitations imposed by wrestling federations that prevented the execution of certain blows and forced the use of gloves.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.adorocinema.com/noticias/series/noticia-138118/|title=Rio Heroes: Série nacional busca evocar a honra na porradaria (Primeiras impressões)|language=Portuguese |date=February 22, 2018 |website=Adoro Cinema}}</ref>
The series is based on a wrestling championship that actually existed between the years 2007 and 2009 and which became known for its extremely crude and violent nature.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.omelete.com.br/series-tv/rio-heroes-aposta-em-violencia-crua-para-contar-historia-de-campeonato-clandestino-de-luta-livre|title=Rio Heroes aposta em violência crua para contar história de campeonato clandestino de luta livre|language=Portuguese |date=February 24, 2018 |website=Omelete}}</ref>
==Premise== The series is based on the real story of the Brazilian wrestler Jorge Pereira, who decided to create a [[Vale tudo]] championship.
